{"query":{"pages":{"46717":{"pageid":46717,"ns":0,"title":"Mission: Borg Disconnected","revisions":[{"*":"<h2><span class=\\"mw-headline\\" id=\\"Notes\\">Notes</span><span class=\\"mw-editsection\\"><span class=\\"mw-editsection-bracket\\">[</span><a href=\\"/index.php?title=Mission:_Borg_Disconnected&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\\" title=\\"Edit section: Notes\\">edit</a><span class=\\"mw-editsection-bracket\\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li> While the mission is available to any player who reach <a href=\\"/Player_rank\\" title=\\"Player rank\\">50+</a>, its story makes more sense following the events of <a href=\\"/Mission:_Into_the_Hive\\" title=\\"Mission: Into the Hive\\">&#8220;Into the Hive&#8221;</a>/<a href=\\"/Mission:_Hive_Onslaught\\" title=\\"Mission: Hive Onslaught\\">&#8220;Hive Onslaught&#8221;</a> and the <a href=\\"/The_Delta_Quadrant\\" title=\\"The Delta Quadrant\\">Delta Quadrant</a> story arc (specifically, <a href=\\"/Mission:_Friends_in_Unlikely_Places\\" title=\\"Mission: Friends in Unlikely Places\\">&#8220;Friends in Unlikely Places&#8221;</a> and <a href=\\"/Mission:_Alliances\\" title=\\"Mission: Alliances\\">&#8220;Alliances&#8221;</a>).\n</li>\n<li> In general, players always receive some rewards for the mission, even if some objectives are not achieved or the mission at large fails. The amount of rewarded marks depends on the performances in the mission and how far the team progressed in it.\n</li>\n<li> In all but the first phase taking care not the draw wide aggro can lead to a single player being able to free ships while drawing minimal fire. The same way a single player holding back while another atracts enemy fire can lead to very fast freeing when working in team.\n</li>\n<li> With the Dreadnoughts on normal a common order used by random teams is Voth, Undine, Borg. On higher difficulty spreading the fire is nessesary.\n</li>\n<li> The Voth Dreadnought is as usually near impossible to break the shields. It needs carefull use of Subnucleonic beam to interrupt his shield heals to break them. As usual the best fallback is shield penetration attacks/shield skipping attacks.\n</li>\n<li> The Undine Dreadnought has the lowest hull, but it is also exceptionally fast wich means a high defense value. That also means it tends to \\"run away\\" from the others if enganged. In order to kill it effectively it's movement should be stopped via Tractor Beams, Gravity Wells and similar powers. It also will spawn Nicor Bioships as usual for it's class.\n</li>\n<li> The Borg queen will regulary use a AoE Placate + Confuse on the players. It can be removed with Science team, but care must be taken that the Borg ship is not still targeted. Also the Borg Dreadnoughts shields seem almost on par with the Voths as far as durability is concerned.\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]}}}}"""))
